00:15.495 --> 00:18.013
Sorry. I couldn't resist.

00:18.015 --> 00:19.281
What, is your back out?

00:19.283 --> 00:22.201
Not yet, but I got a big date
for Valentine's Day.

00:22.203 --> 00:25.621
And if everything goes well,
I'll need a chiropractor,

00:25.623 --> 00:28.073
a psychiatrist and a priest.

00:28.925 --> 00:30.042
I can't wait for this

00:30.044 --> 00:31.293
stupid holiday
to be over

00:31.295 --> 00:32.762
so we can celebrate
something cool, like...

00:32.764 --> 00:35.765
Free Bobblehead
at Dodger Stadium Day.

00:36.583 --> 00:38.017
What are you
talking about?

00:38.019 --> 00:39.418
Valentine's Day.

00:39.420 --> 00:40.853
Or what it should really
be called:

00:40.855 --> 00:42.754
Dumb Greeting Card,
Chocolate-Covered,

00:42.756 --> 00:45.257
Overpriced Flowers,
Can't Get a Dinner Reservation,

00:45.259 --> 00:48.760
I'm Probably Going
to Die Alone Anyway Day.

00:48.762 --> 00:51.280
Sounds like
Cupid's arrow hit somebody

00:51.282 --> 00:52.581
right in the
the bile sack.

00:52.583 --> 00:55.568
Don't get my started
on that fat, flying baby.

00:55.570 --> 00:57.453
What could you possibly have
against Cupid?

00:57.455 --> 00:59.955
First of all,
he's wearing a diaper.

00:59.957 --> 01:01.874
Yeah, that's sexy.

01:01.876 --> 01:03.275
And then he's got wings,

01:03.277 --> 01:05.777
which make you think of angels,
which makes you think of God,

01:05.779 --> 01:06.879
which makes you feel guilty

01:06.881 --> 01:08.581
about having sex
in the first place.

01:08.583 --> 01:10.666
And in the second place.

01:12.135 --> 01:15.287
Well, I, for one, am going
all out for Lyndsey this year.

01:15.289 --> 01:16.972
Really?
What's that mean?

01:16.974 --> 01:20.092
Cemetery flowers and a coupon
for one free go-around

01:20.094 --> 01:22.478
on Mr. Alan's Wild Ride?

01:22.480 --> 01:23.846
I am sparing no expense.

01:23.848 --> 01:24.930
Lyndsey deserves the best,

01:24.932 --> 01:27.016
and I am finally going
to give it to her.

01:27.018 --> 01:28.517
Well, if you're
giving it to her,

01:28.519 --> 01:30.186
it's not going to be the best.

01:32.606 --> 01:34.806
(cell phone chimes)

01:34.808 --> 01:36.158
Wow.

01:36.160 --> 01:37.193
What?

01:37.195 --> 01:39.795
I just got an e-mail from Kate.

01:39.797 --> 01:41.580
She's in town.
She wants to see me.

01:41.582 --> 01:42.648
Did she say why?

01:42.650 --> 01:44.200
No.

01:44.202 --> 01:46.318
Could be anything.

01:46.320 --> 01:47.819
It could be nothing.

01:47.821 --> 01:49.655
Could be something.

01:49.657 --> 01:51.006
Could be something serious.

01:51.008 --> 01:52.842
What if she's dying?

01:52.844 --> 01:54.477
What if she's pregnant?

01:54.479 --> 01:57.496
Wait, what if she's dying
to be pregnant?

01:57.498 --> 02:00.299
The woman I love
wants to have my child.

02:00.301 --> 02:02.935
Oh, my God,
I'm going to be a father.

02:02.937 --> 02:06.055
Advantage: fat, flying baby.

02:07.524 --> 02:09.692
